---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import IntegrationFlowWidget from '../components/IntegrationFlowWidget';
---

<Layout
  title="DCIM Integration - Connect Nlyte, Sunbird & Schneider to Indian Billing"
  description="Add Indian billing intelligence to your existing DCIM. BharatDCIM integrates with Nlyte Software, Sunbird dcTrack, and Schneider EcoStruxure IT for ToD tariff billing, DG metering, and GST invoicing."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-mesh-strong section-xl">
    <div class="glow-orb glow-orb-primary w-[28rem] h-[28rem] -top-40 -right-40"></div>
    <div class="glow-orb glow-orb-accent w-96 h-96 top-16 -left-52"></div>
    <div class="container relative">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <span class="section-label">Enterprise Integration</span>
        <h1 class="hero-title mb-6">
          Add Indian Billing Intelligence
          <span class="block text-[#8b2e3e]">to Your Existing DCIM</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          BharatDCIM connects to Nlyte Software, Sunbird dcTrack, and Schneider EcoStruxure IT in minutes. Turn raw power data into ToD-aware, GST-compliant tenant invoices.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mb-8 justify-center">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-4">Book Integration Demo</a>
          <a href="#how-it-works" class="btn-secondary text-lg px-8 py-4">See How It Works</a>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 justify-center">
          <span class="badge-chip">One-touch setup</span>
          <span class="badge-chip">API + SNMP + CSV</span>
          <span class="badge-chip">No rip and replace</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust Strip -->
  <section class="section-tight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="trust-strip max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="trust-logo-pill">Works with Nlyte Software</div>
        <div class="trust-logo-pill">Works with Sunbird dcTrack</div>
        <div class="trust-logo-pill">Works with EcoStruxure IT</div>
        <div class="trust-logo-pill">Works with any DCIM via API</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Visual Break -->
  <div class="relative h-40 md:h-56 overflow-hidden">
    <img src="/images/hero-bg.jpg" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover blur-md scale-110" loading="lazy" />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1e3a5f]/80 via-[#1e3a5f]/40 to-[#1e3a5f]/80"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center">
      <p class="text-white/90 text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold tracking-wide text-center px-4">
        Your DCIM tells you what's consuming power. BharatDCIM tells you what to charge for it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- The Gap -->
  <section class="section relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-white via-gray-50/50 to-white"></div>
    <div class="container relative">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center mb-16">
        <span class="section-label">The Gap</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">
          Your DCIM Knows the Power.
          <span class="block accent">Not the Price.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-gray-50 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-[#1e3a5f]/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[#1e3a5f]" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 0 1 3 19.875v-6.75ZM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 0 1-1.125-1.125V8.625ZM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 0 1-1.125-1.125V4.125Z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">Global DCIM Tracks Consumption</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Nlyte Software, Sunbird dcTrack, and EcoStruxure IT excel at asset management, capacity planning, and power monitoring. They tell you Rack A7 consumed 850 kWh this month.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-gray-50 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-[#8b2e3e]/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[#8b2e3e]" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">But Not Indian Billing Logic</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            They can't tell you that 300 kWh was during MSEDCL evening peak at +Rs.1.10/kVAh, or that 50 kWh came from DG at Rs.22/kWh.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-gray-50 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-amber-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-amber-600" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126ZM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008Z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">The Result: Excel Fills the Gap</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Operations teams manually export data, apply ToD rates in spreadsheets, and generate invoices by hand. Every month.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interactive Integration Widget -->
  <section id="how-it-works" class="section-tight bg-mesh">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center mb-10">
        <span class="section-label">How It Works</span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          One-Touch Integration
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <IntegrationFlowWidget client:visible />
        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 text-sm mt-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          BharatDCIM ingests power readings from your existing DCIM and applies Indian billing intelligence automatically.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Better Together Comparison -->
  <section class="section relative overflow-hidden bg-mesh-cool">
    <div class="container relative">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="section-label">Better Together</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">
          Complete Indian
          <span class="block accent">DC Operations</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="bg-[#1e3a5f] text-white text-left px-6 py-4 rounded-tl-xl text-sm font-semibold">Your Existing DCIM Handles</th>
              <th class="bg-[#8b2e3e] text-white text-left px-6 py-4 rounded-tr-xl text-sm font-semibold">BharatDCIM Adds</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-sm">
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600 bg-white">Asset Lifecycle Management</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-900 font-medium bg-[#8b2e3e]/[0.03]">ToD Tariff Billing</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600 bg-white">Capacity Planning</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-900 font-medium bg-[#8b2e3e]/[0.03]">DG vs Grid Metering</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600 bg-white">Power Monitoring</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-900 font-medium bg-[#8b2e3e]/[0.03]">GST Invoice Generation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600 bg-white">3D Visualization</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-900 font-medium bg-[#8b2e3e]/[0.03]">State-wise Compliance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600 bg-white">Change Management</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-900 font-medium bg-[#8b2e3e]/[0.03]">Admin Dashboard & Billing</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600 bg-white rounded-bl-xl">CMDB Integration</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-900 font-medium bg-[#8b2e3e]/[0.03] rounded-br-xl">GST Invoice Generation</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Setup Steps -->
  <section class="section-tight bg-mesh">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center mb-10">
        <span class="section-label">Setup</span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          Live in Under a Week
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step-number mb-4">01</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Connect</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Import data via CSV exports from your DCIM (Nlyte, Sunbird, EcoStruxure formats auto-detected), connect our SNMP v2c polling agent to your PDUs, or use our REST API.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step-number mb-4">02</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Configure</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Select your states and tariff profiles. We pre-load official rates from MERC, TNERC, KERC, and TSERC.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <span class="process-step-number mb-4">03</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Go Live</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">BharatDCIM starts classifying consumption by ToD slot and generating GST-compliant invoices automatically.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder's Vision -->
  <section class="section relative bg-mesh-cool">
    <div class="container relative">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <span class="section-label text-center block">Why We Built This</span>
        <h2 class="section-title text-center mb-10">
          The Problem We're
          <span class="block accent">Solving</span>
        </h2>

        <div class="card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-gray-50 p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Indian data center operators face a billing challenge that no global DCIM addresses:
              <strong>Time-of-Day tariffs, state-specific regulatory structures, kWh vs kVAh billing,
              DG cost pass-through, and GST compliance</strong> — all in a single invoice.
            </p>
            <p>
              Today, most operators bridge this gap with spreadsheets. Finance teams spend days
              each month manually classifying consumption into ToD slots, applying the right
              surcharges, splitting DG costs, and generating GST-compliant invoices.
            </p>
            <p>
              BharatDCIM exists to eliminate that manual work. We've encoded the tariff structures
              of Maharashtra, Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, and Telangana into a billing engine that
              classifies consumption, applies the correct rates, and generates invoices automatically.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-medium">
              Our goal: any Indian data center operator should be able to go from raw meter data
              to accurate, auditable, GST-compliant tenant invoices — without touching a spreadsheet.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#1e3a5f] via-[#162d4a] to-[#1e3a5f]"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 dot-grid opacity-10"></div>
    <div class="container relative py-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center text-white">
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-white/60 mb-4 block">Next Step</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
          Connect Your DCIM This Week
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/80 mb-8">
          Schedule a 30-minute integration assessment. We'll map your current DCIM setup and show you exactly how BharatDCIM plugs in.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-light text-lg px-8 py-4">Book Integration Demo</a>
        <p class="text-xs text-white/60 mt-6">No rip-and-replace. No vendor lock-in. Just Indian billing intelligence.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="section-tight relative overflow-hidden bg-mesh-cool">
    <div class="glow-orb glow-orb-accent w-72 h-72 -bottom-36 right-10"></div>
    <div class="container relative">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="section-label">FAQ</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">
          Integration<br />
          <span class="accent">Questions</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-4">
        <details class="faq-item" open>
          <summary>How long does integration take?</summary>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
            CSV import can start on day one — just export from your existing DCIM and upload. SNMP v2c polling setup typically takes 2-3 days for PDU discovery and OID mapping. Most operators are fully live within a week.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do I need to replace my existing DCIM?</summary>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
            No. BharatDCIM is designed to complement your existing DCIM, not replace it. Your Nlyte, Sunbird, or Schneider installation continues handling asset management, capacity planning, and infrastructure monitoring. BharatDCIM adds the Indian billing layer on top.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which DCIM platforms do you support?</summary>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
            We support CSV imports from Nlyte Software, Sunbird dcTrack, and Schneider EcoStruxure IT — our pipeline auto-detects the format from column headers. We also poll smart PDUs (APC, Raritan, Server Technology) directly via SNMP v2c, and offer a REST API for custom integrations.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What if my DCIM isn't listed?</summary>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
            Any system that can export power consumption data as CSV can integrate with BharatDCIM. We also support SNMP v2c polling for direct PDU monitoring and a REST API for programmatic data submission. Contact us for a custom integration assessment.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structured Data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does DCIM integration take?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "CSV import can start on day one — just export from your existing DCIM and upload. SNMP v2c polling setup typically takes 2-3 days for PDU discovery and OID mapping. Most operators are fully live within a week."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need to replace my existing DCIM?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. BharatDCIM is designed to complement your existing DCIM, not replace it. Your Nlyte, Sunbird, or Schneider installation continues handling asset management, capacity planning, and infrastructure monitoring. BharatDCIM adds the Indian billing layer on top."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which DCIM platforms does BharatDCIM support?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "We support CSV imports from Nlyte Software, Sunbird dcTrack, and Schneider EcoStruxure IT — our pipeline auto-detects the format from column headers. We also poll smart PDUs (APC, Raritan, Server Technology) directly via SNMP v2c, and offer a REST API for custom integrations."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What if my DCIM platform isn't listed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Any system that can export power consumption data as CSV can integrate with BharatDCIM. We also support SNMP v2c polling for direct PDU monitoring and a REST API for programmatic data submission. Contact us for a custom integration assessment."
        }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
    "name": "BharatDCIM",
    "applicationCategory": "BusinessApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Web",
    "description": "Add Indian billing intelligence to your existing DCIM. BharatDCIM integrates with Nlyte Software, Sunbird dcTrack, and Schneider EcoStruxure IT for ToD tariff billing, DG metering, and GST invoicing.",
    "featureList": [
      "CSV Import from Nlyte, Sunbird, EcoStruxure (auto-detected)",
      "SNMP v2c PDU Polling (APC, Raritan, Server Technology)",
      "REST API for Custom Integrations",
      "ToD-Aware Billing Engine",
      "GST-Compliant Invoice Generation",
      "Multi-State Tariff Support (MH, TN, KA, TS)"
    ],
    "provider": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "BharatDCIM",
      "url": "https://bharatdcim.com"
    }
  })} />
</Layout>
